            <fr:uri>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JV/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>jms-00JV</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/jms-00JV/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="The adjacency matrix of the reflexive-transitive closure">The <fr:link href="/jms-00JN/" title="Adjacency matrix of a finite directed graph" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JN/" display-uri="jms-00JN" type="local">adjacency matrix</fr:link> of the <fr:link href="/jms-00JH/" title="The reflexive-transitive closure of an endo-relation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JH/" display-uri="jms-00JH" type="local">reflexive-transitive closure</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Algorithm</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M = \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R]]></fr:tex> be the <fr:link href="/jms-00JN/" title="Adjacency matrix of a finite directed graph" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JN/" display-uri="jms-00JN" type="local">adjacency matrix</fr:link> of a  finite <fr:link href="/jms-00JC/" title="Directed graph" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JC/" display-uri="jms-00JC" type="local">directed graph</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left ({\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}},R\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. We will show that the <fr:link href="/jms-00JN/" title="Adjacency matrix of a finite directed graph" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JN/" display-uri="jms-00JN" type="local">adjacency matrix</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M^*]]></fr:tex> of the <fr:link href="/jms-00JH/" title="The reflexive-transitive closure of an endo-relation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JH/" display-uri="jms-00JH" type="local">reflexive-transitive closure</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R^{\circ *}]]></fr:tex> can be computed recursively using the <fr:link href="/jms-00JS/" title="Adding matrices together" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JS/" display-uri="jms-00JS" type="local">additive</fr:link> and <fr:link href="/jms-00IW/" title="Multiplication of matrices" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IW/" display-uri="jms-00IW" type="local">multiplicative</fr:link> structure of <fr:link href="/jms-00IS/" title="Matrix over a semiring" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IS/" display-uri="jms-00IS" type="local">matrices</fr:link>. In particular, we can define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M^* = M_n]]></fr:tex> where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M_k]]></fr:tex> is computed recursively as below:</html:p><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 \begin {aligned}
   M_0 &= I^n\\
   M_{k+1} &= I^n \oplus  {\mathopen {}\left (M\otimes  M_k\right )\mathclose {}}
 \end {aligned}
]]></fr:tex><html:p>Thus we have a recursive algorithm that can deicde whether there is a path between two elements in a finite <fr:link href="/jms-00JC/" title="Directed graph" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JC/" display-uri="jms-00JC" type="local">directed graph</fr:link>: indeed, there is a path from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[t]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M^*_{s,t} =\mathsf {true}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>21</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>We first unravel the first few <html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M_k]]></fr:tex>â€™s</html:span> to get a better understanding.</html:p>

 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {aligned}
   M_1 &= I^n \oplus  {\mathopen {}\left (M\otimes  M_0\right )\mathclose {}}
   \\
   &= I^n\oplus  {\mathopen {}\left (M\otimes  I^n\right )\mathclose {}}
   \\
   &= I^n \oplus  M
   \\
   M_2 &= I^n \oplus  {\mathopen {}\left (M\otimes  M_1\right )\mathclose {}}
   \\
   &= I^n \oplus  {\mathopen {}\left (M\otimes  {\mathopen {}\left (I^n \oplus  M\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}
   \\
   &= I^n \oplus  {\mathopen {}\left (M\otimes  I^n\right )\mathclose {}} \oplus  {\mathopen {}\left (M\otimes  M\right )\mathclose {}}
   \\
   &= I^n \oplus  M \oplus  M^2
  \end {aligned}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <html:p>By induction, we can extend the pattern above to a closed form for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M_k]]></fr:tex>. In particular, we deduce that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M_k = \bigoplus _{l\leq  k} M^l]]></fr:tex> by recalling from <fr:link href="/jms-00J3/" title="Associativity and unit laws of matrix products" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00J3/" display-uri="jms-00J3" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00J3/" display-uri="jms-00J3" /></fr:link> that the <fr:link href="/jms-00IT/" title="The identity matrix" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IT/" display-uri="jms-00IT" type="local">identity matrix</fr:link> is the neutral element for <fr:link href="/jms-00IV/" title="Product of matrices" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IV/" display-uri="jms-00IV" type="local">matrix multiplication</fr:link>. Therefore, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M_n =\bigoplus _{k \leq  n}M^k]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>

 <html:p>Our goal is to show that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M_n = \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}} R^{\circ  *}]]></fr:tex>; we have already seen in <fr:link href="/jms-00JR/" title="matrix addition and union of relations" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JR/" display-uri="jms-00JR" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JR/" display-uri="jms-00JR" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="/jms-00J2/" title="matrix product is relational composition" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00J2/" display-uri="jms-00J2" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00J2/" display-uri="jms-00J2" /></fr:link> that <fr:link href="/jms-00JO/" title="Pointwise addition of matrices" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JO/" display-uri="jms-00JO" type="local">matrix addition</fr:link> corresponds to union of <fr:link href="/jms-00I7/" title="Relation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7/" display-uri="jms-00I7" type="local">relations</fr:link> and <fr:link href="/jms-00IV/" title="Product of matrices" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IV/" display-uri="jms-00IV" type="local">matrix multiplication</fr:link> corresponds to <fr:link href="/jms-00IN/" title="Relational composite" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IN/" display-uri="jms-00IN" type="local">relational composition</fr:link>.</html:p>

 <html:p>By <fr:link href="/jms-00JU/" title="Reflexive-transitive closure of finite endo-relations" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JU/" display-uri="jms-00JU" type="local">Observation <fr:contextual-number uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JU/" display-uri="jms-00JU" /></fr:link> (<fr:link href="/jms-00JU/" title="Reflexive-transitive closure of finite endo-relations" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JU/" display-uri="jms-00JU" type="local">Reflexive-transitive closure of <html:em>finite</html:em> <fr:link href="/jms-00JF/" title="Path in a directed graph" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JF/" display-uri="jms-00JF" type="local">endo-relations</fr:link></fr:link>), we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R^{\circ *} = \bigcup _{k\leq  n} R^{\circ  k}]]></fr:tex>. Therefore:</html:p>

 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R^{\circ *} = \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}\bigcup _{k\leq  n} R^{\circ  k}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <html:p>By <fr:link href="/jms-00JR/" title="matrix addition and union of relations" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JR/" display-uri="jms-00JR" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JR/" display-uri="jms-00JR" /></fr:link> (<fr:link href="/jms-00JR/" title="matrix addition and union of relations" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JR/" display-uri="jms-00JR" type="local"><fr:link href="/jms-00JO/" title="Pointwise addition of matrices" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JO/" display-uri="jms-00JO" type="local">matrix addition</fr:link> and union of <fr:link href="/jms-00I7/" title="Relation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7/" display-uri="jms-00I7" type="local">relations</fr:link></fr:link>), we have:</html:p>

 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}\bigcup _{k\leq  n} R^{\circ  k}
  =
  \bigoplus _{k\leq  n} \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R^{\circ  k}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 By <fr:link href="/jms-00J2/" title="matrix product is relational composition" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00J2/" display-uri="jms-00J2" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00J2/" display-uri="jms-00J2" /></fr:link> (<fr:link href="/jms-00J2/" title="matrix product is relational composition" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00J2/" display-uri="jms-00J2" type="local"><fr:link href="/jms-00IV/" title="Product of matrices" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IV/" display-uri="jms-00IV" type="local">matrix product</fr:link> is <fr:link href="/jms-00IN/" title="Relational composite" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IN/" display-uri="jms-00IN" type="local">relational composition</fr:link></fr:link>), we have:
 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \bigoplus _{k\leq  n} \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R^{\circ  k}  =
  \bigoplus _{k\leq  n} {\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R\right )\mathclose {}}^k
  =
  \bigoplus _{k\leq  n} M^k
  = M_n
 ]]></fr:tex>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
